@samdark 
Of course it could be done from framework-side. My PR can resolve it.

@cebe 

> The proposed PR adds @property tags. This is not enough as these would get removed because not corresponding getters/setters exist.

Why we need getter/setter must exist? Your model generator (gii) can generate `@property` tags for every columns in table without any getter/setter.
If we realy need getter/setter for `@property` tags, then we must move `getRequest()` from base application to both console application and web application.
